          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τάλαντον</span></b>  (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ταλ, τλῆναι</span>): (1) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">scale</span>, pl.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">scales, balance</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            12.433</span></i>; esp. fig., of the golden scales in which Zeus
          balances the fates of men, <i><span class="en">Il. 8.69</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 16.658</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 19.223</span></i>.—(2) a definite (unknown)
          weight, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">talent</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χρῡσοῖο</span>, <i><span class="en">*i 122</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.129</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
